Fed’s Bullard Calls Europe Crisis ‘Top Threat’ to U.S. Economy

-- B y   S t e v e   M a t t h e w s
-- 
2011-05-24T18:29:35Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-24/fed-s-bullard-calls-europe-crisis-top-threat-to-u-s-economy.html
Federal Reserve Bank of St. Louis
President  James Bullard  said he believes  Europe ’s sovereign-debt
crisis poses the biggest threat to the U.S. economic recovery.  “It is the top threat to the  U.S. economy  today,” Bullard
said today in response to audience questions after a speech in
Cape Girardeau,  Missouri . “The European policy makers have
tremendous resolve” to back the euro, he said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Steve Matthews  in Atlanta at 
 smatthews@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editors responsible for this story:
Christopher Wellisz at 
 cwellisz@bloomberg.net  